<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Publickey on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/publickey/</link><description>Recent content in Publickey on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/publickey/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Git Permission Denied SSH — Permission denied (publickey)</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/git/permission-denied2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/git/permission-denied2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="git-permission-denied-ssh--permission-denied-publickey"&gt;Git Permission Denied SSH — Permission denied (publickey)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when SSH authentication fails when connecting to a Git remote. The server rejects your SSH key or credentials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SSH key not added to the SSH agent&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Public key not added to the Git hosting service (GitHub, GitLab)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong SSH key being used&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SSH key permissions are too open&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="check-ssh-agent"&gt;Check SSH Agent&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;eval &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;ssh-agent -s&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="test-ssh-connection"&gt;Test SSH Connection&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh -T git@github.com
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="verify-ssh-key-is-added"&gt;Verify SSH Key is Added&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh-add -l
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-ssh-key-permissions"&gt;Fix SSH Key Permissions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;700&lt;/span&gt; ~/.ssh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;600&lt;/span&gt; ~/.ssh/id_rsa
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;chmod &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;644&lt;/span&gt; ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="use-https-instead-of-ssh"&gt;Use HTTPS Instead of SSH&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git remote set-url origin https://github.com/user/repo.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="generate-new-ssh-key"&gt;Generate New SSH Key&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;your_email@example.com&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 1: SSH key not in agent&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git push origin main
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Permission denied (publickey).&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Fix: eval &amp;#34;$(ssh-agent -s)&amp;#34; &amp;amp;&amp;amp; ssh-add ~/.ssh/id_rsa&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 2: Test SSH connection&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ssh -T git@github.com
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Hi username! You&amp;#39;ve successfully authenticated&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Example 3: Switch to HTTPS&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git remote set-url origin https://github.com/user/repo.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git push origin main
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/git/push-rejected/"&gt;Push Rejected&lt;/a&gt; — remote has changes you don&amp;rsquo;t have&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tools/docker/permission-denied3/"&gt;Permission Denied&lt;/a&gt; — Docker permission issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux SSH Permission Denied — Authentication Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-ssh-permission-denied/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-ssh-permission-denied/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-ssh-permission-denied"&gt;Linux: SSH Permission denied&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;Permission denied (publickey)&lt;/code&gt; error means the SSH server rejected all authentication methods offered by the client. This typically means your SSH key was not accepted (not in &lt;code&gt;authorized_keys&lt;/code&gt;), or password authentication is disabled.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SSH public key not added to &lt;code&gt;~/.ssh/authorized_keys&lt;/code&gt; on the server&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Incorrect permissions on &lt;code&gt;~/.ssh&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;authorized_keys&lt;/code&gt; on either side&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;PasswordAuthentication&lt;/code&gt; set to &lt;code&gt;no&lt;/code&gt; in sshd_config&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;PubkeyAuthentication&lt;/code&gt; set to &lt;code&gt;no&lt;/code&gt; in sshd_config&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wrong username used for authentication&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SELinux blocking SSH key access&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-ssh-server-configuration"&gt;1. Check SSH Server Configuration&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# On the server, check authentication settings&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;sudo grep -E &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;PubkeyAuthentication|PasswordAuthentication|PermitRootLogin|AuthorizedKeysFile&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; /etc/ssh/sshd_config
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Ensure these settings:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# PubkeyAuthentication yes&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# PasswordAuthentication yes (if you want password login)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# AuthorizedKeysFile .ssh/authorized_keys&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-fix-ssh-directory-and-file-permissions"&gt;2. Fix SSH Directory and File Permissions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;On the server:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux SSH Permission Denied — publickey,password Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-ssh-permission-denied-v2/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/linux-ssh-permission-denied-v2/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-ssh--permission-denied-publickeypassword"&gt;Linux: SSH — Permission denied (publickey,password)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;Permission denied (publickey,password)&lt;/code&gt; error means the SSH server rejected the client&amp;rsquo;s authentication attempt. The server offered publickey and/or password authentication methods, but the client&amp;rsquo;s credentials were not accepted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SSH uses a challenge-response authentication system. The server checks whether the connecting user&amp;rsquo;s public key is in &lt;code&gt;~/.ssh/authorized_keys&lt;/code&gt; (for key auth) or whether the password matches the system password. If neither method succeeds, the server logs &lt;code&gt;Permission denied&lt;/code&gt; and closes the connection.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>